The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 August is 295,110 (34,013.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 August, there were 391 new confirmed cases (45.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 August, there were 463 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (72 fewer cases).
